# Emacs as a Window Manager
# test
If you hate never used Emacs before I highly recommend reading a begginers guide. Below are a few rather usefull tutorials.

http://www.jesshamrick.com/2012/09/10/absolute-beginners-guide-to-emacs/

http://ergoemacs.org/emacs/emacs.html

https://www.gnu.org/software/emacs/tour/

Once you have a working knowledge of how Emacs behaves, the following is a list of commands for navigating and controlling Emacs as a window manager.

1. Installing multiterm.

M-x list-packages

A buffer called Packages should now appear - from the list find mult-term, highlight and press enter. Click or highlight install and press enter.
